>   A minister passing through his church in the
> middle of the day, Decided to
>  >
>  > pause by the altar and see who had come to pray.
>  >
>  > Just then the back door opened, a man came down
> the aisle, The minister
>  > frowned as he saw the man hadn't shaved in a
> while.
>  >
>  > His shirt was kinda shabby and his coat was worn
> and frayed, the man
>  > knelt,
>  > he bowed his head, then rose and walked away.
>  >
>  > In the days that followed, each noon time came
> this chap, each time he
>  > knelt
>  > just for a moment, a lunch pail in his lap.
>  >
>  > Well, the minister's suspicions grew, with
> robbery a main fear, He decided
>  > to
>  > stop the man and ask him, "What are you doing
> here?"
>  >
>  > The old man said, he worked down the road. Lunch
> was half an hour.
>  > Lunchtime
>  > was his prayer time, for finding strength and
> power.
>  >
>  > "I stay only moments, see, because the factory is
